text.section:
The Commission shall:
Establish policies directed toward the Maryland Aviation Administration's ability to improve and promote the role of the Baltimore-Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport as an airport of service to the Washington-Baltimore metropolitan area;
Approve regulations for the operation of the State-owned airports prior to their adoption by the Executive Director;
Direct the Administration in developing and implementing airport management policy for all State-owned airports;
Approve major capital projects, as defined in § 2-103.1(a)(4) of this article, at any State-owned airport prior to the submission of those projects to the Governor and General Assembly for approval;
Exercise those powers granted to the Commission by this title or by any other provision of law; and
In carrying out the provisions of this subtitle, consider information and advice from the air carrier industry, the airport concessionaire industry, the airline support services industry, and citizen advisory groups.

section.section:
Subject to the provisions of paragraph (3) of this subsection, the Governor may not appoint to the Commission:
An officer or employee of the State, except as provided in subsection (c) of this section;
A representative of any entity whose principal activities are related to the operation of State-owned airports;
A person employed by any entity whose principal activities are related to the operation of State-owned airports; or
A member of the General Assembly.
